"""
cdv_digitized_data.py

Digitized (Total Deduct Value, Corrected Deduct Value) points for the
ASTM D6433 Corrected Deduct Value (CDV) correction curves (Fig. X3.26
for asphalt, Fig. X4.20 for concrete).

The correction curves are a FAMILY of curves, one per q value, where:
    q = number of individual deduct values greater than 2.0

So unlike the distress curves (which are indexed by distress type +
severity), these are indexed solely by q (integer, 1 through 8+).

X-axis : Total Deduct Value (TDV), linear scale, roughly 0 to 200
Y-axis : Corrected Deduct Value (CDV), linear scale, 0 to 100

*** PLACEHOLDER DATA ***
Replace the arrays below with your own digitized points from
WebPlotDigitizer or similar. The structure must stay the same:
    CDV_POINTS[q] = {"tdv": [...], "cdv": [...]}

The q=1 curve is special: CDV = TDV (no correction needed when only one
deduct value exceeds 2), so it is a straight line through the origin
with slope 1.
"""

